div.h3: How I got to solving the Rubik’s cube in under 30 seconds
div.p: About six months ago I wrote a blog post about how I got to solving the Rubik’s cube in under 60 seconds consistently. Since then, I have been working on improving and getting even faster solves.

div.h3: Unraveling the Magic of Composition over Inheritance
div.p: “Composition over inheritance” is a principle in programming that emphasizes the use of object composition instead of class inheritance to achieve code maintainability. While inheritance can be useful in certain scenarios, it can also lead to tight coupling and inflexible designs.

div.h3: Better PHPUnit CLI output with Collision
div.p: I really like how Pest PHP formats and outputs test results, but I still prefer to use PHPUnit. Luckily there’s Collision. This package is designed to give you beautiful error reporting when interacting with your app through the command line.

div.h3: Enforcing minimum code coverage with PHPUnit
div.p: The new major release of PHPUnit gives developers the opportunity to extend it by using the event system. This allows us to create extensions and build upon the core functionality of PHPUnit.
